        <p><a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/about/index.php"><strong>University of Aberdeen</strong></a>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>The University had a museum as far back as 1727 (almost 300 years) and holds a huge range of collections that cover its full history. The collections range from archaeology and ethnography to Scottish history, coins and medals, fine art, scientific instruments, medicine, natural sciences and more.</p>
        <p>Visit the collections online at <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/collections/index.php">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/collections/index.php</a>&nbsp; or read more about the museums&rsquo; work on their blog: <a href="https://library.abdn.ac.uk/blog/">https://library.abdn.ac.uk/blog/</a> You can find out more about their exhibitions and events at <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/news-events.php">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/news-events.php</a></p>
        <p><em>Visiting:</em></p>
        <p>For general information on visiting the museums, including accessibility information, see <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/about/visit-us.php">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/about/visit-us.php</a></p>
        <p>There are three museums within the University campus:</p>
        <p><a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/sdrl-679.php"><strong><em>The Gallery in the Sir Duncan Rice Library</em></strong></a></p>
        <p>The Gallery has a programme of changing exhibitions throughout the year taken from the University&rsquo;s huge collection. You don&rsquo;t need to book and entry is free. For information on the latest exhibitions, visit <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/index.php">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/index.php</a></p>
        <p><em>Address:</em></p>
        <p>Bedford Road, Aberdeen AB24 3AA</p>
        <p><em>Opening hours:</em></p>
        <p>Mon &ndash; Wed, Fri: 10am &ndash; 5pm; Thurs: 10am &ndash; 7pm; Sat &amp; Sun: 11am &ndash; 4pm</p>
        <p><em>Getting there:</em></p>
        <p>Parking on site is reserved for university staff, but there is pay and display parking in the surrounding roads. For directions and further information on how to get there, visit <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/about/campus/maps/view/112/">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/about/campus/maps/view/112/</a></p>
        <p><em>Public transport: </em></p>
        <p>The no. 19 bus stops directly outside the Sir Duncan Rice Library on Bedford Road, and runs every 15 minutes.&nbsp; Bus routes 1, 2 and 20 also stop at the University campus. See First Bus timetables <a href="https://www.firstgroup.com/aberdeen/routes-and-maps/route-maps">https://www.firstgroup.com/aberdeen/routes-and-maps/route-maps</a></p>
        <p>For a pan-disability access guide to the Sir Duncan Rice Library, visit the <a href="https://www.accessable.co.uk/university-of-aberdeen/old-aberdeen-campus/access-guides/sir-duncan-rice-library">AccessAble</a> website.</p>
        <p><a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/zoology-museum-588.php"><strong><em>Zoology Museum</em></strong></a></p>
        <p>The museum houses the only large, international exhibition of zoological specimens in the north of Scotland. You can see insects, birds and even whales and tigers. You don&rsquo;t need to book and entry is free. For more information, visit <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/zoology-museum-588.php">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/zoology-museum-588.php</a></p>
        <p><em>Address:</em></p>
        <p>Tillydrone Ave, Aberdeen AB24 2TZ</p>
        <p><em>Opening hours: </em></p>
        <p>Mon &ndash; Fri: 10am &ndash; 5pm</p>
        <p><em>Getting there:</em></p>
        <p>Parking on site is reserved for university staff, but there is pay and display parking in the surrounding roads. For directions and further information on how to get there, visit <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/about/campus/maps/view/113/">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/about/campus/maps/view/113/</a></p>
        <p>Access to the upper floor of the museum is limited &ndash; contact the museum for details. For a pan-disability access guide to the Zoology building, visit the <a href="https://www.accessable.co.uk/university-of-aberdeen/old-aberdeen-campus/access-guides/zoology-building">AccessAble</a> website.</p>
        <p><a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/museums/exhibitions/kings-museum-586.php"><strong><em>King&rsquo;s Museum</em></strong></a><strong><em>, Old Aberdeen Town House</em></strong></p>
        <p>Currently closed for re-development, this small museum will be re-opening in September 2020 with a permanent display about the history of the University of Aberdeen and the Old Aberdeen area.</p>
        <p><em>Address:</em></p>
        <p>Old Aberdeen Town House, High Street, Aberdeen AB24 3EN</p>
        <p><strong><em>Group and school visits:</em></strong></p>
        <p>For group or school visits to the Sir Duncan Rice Library Gallery, you can email Susan Curran, Curator of Learning and Outreach, on <a href="mailto:susan.curran@abdn.ac.uk">susan.curran@abdn.ac.uk</a> or call 01224 274354.</p>
        <p>For group and school visits to the Zoology Museum, please contact the Aberdeen Biodiversity Centre on <a href="mailto:biodiversity@abdn.ac.uk">biodiversity@abdn.ac.uk</a> or call 01224 274545 <a href="https://www.abdn.ac.uk/biodiversity/">https://www.abdn.ac.uk/biodiversity/</a></p>
        <p><strong><em>Research visits:</em></strong></p>
        <p>To arrange a research visit, please contact <a href="mailto:museum@abdn.ac.uk">museum@abdn.ac.uk</a> or call 01224 274300.</p>
